## Privacy and data

### What Cy sees
- Everything in the family's Trellis account
- Calendar integration data (if connected)
- Notes, tasks, family meeting outputs

### What Cy doesn't see
- Data from other families
- Data from before the family joined Trellis (no backward import)
- Data outside of Trellis (emails, texts, browser history)

### What Cy remembers
- Everything in the family's account, indefinitely (until they
  delete it)
- Patterns within the family's own data

### What Cy doesn't remember
- Conversations with other families
- Anything outside the current family's scope

### What leaves the family's account
- Nothing is used to train AI models
- Nothing is sold to third parties
- Nothing leaves the family's Trellis account except aggregated,
  anonymized metrics (e.g., "the average family does 40 tasks a
  week") for our internal metrics — never with personal detail

